reference.shortdesc:
The SQRT function returns the square root of a floating-point number;
only the built-in types REAL, FLOAT, and DOUBLE PRECISION are
supported.

codeblock.b:
-- throws an exception if any row stores a negative number: VALUES SQRT(3421E+09)
-- returns the square root of an INTEGER after casting it as a -- floating-point data type: SELECT SQRT(myDoubleColumn) FROM MyTable
VALUES SQRT (CAST(25 AS FLOAT));
